title: Candidate attacks opponent for not arresting Cosby in 2005
text: > Pennsylvania Candidate attacks opponent for not arresting Cosby in 2005 FILE - In this Aug. 8, 2015 file photo, the first assistant district attorney of Montgomery County, Pa., Kevin R. Steele, arrives at the county detective bureau in Norristown, Pa. Steele, Democratic challenger for district attorney in suburban Philadelphia, is running a TV ad criticizing his opponent, former Montgomery County prosecutor Bruce L. Castor Jr., for not bringing charges against comedian Bill Cosby when the sexual assault allegations first surfaced a decade ago. (AP Photo/Matt Rourke, File)
